Section 1:
1 L.D. 98
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 EDUCATION AND CULTURAL AFFAIRS
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 63, L.D. 98, “An Act to Include School
10 Counselors in the Educators for Maine Program”
11 Amend the bill by inserting after section 1 the following:
12 'Sec. 2. 20-A MRSA §12501-A, sub-§12-A is enacted to read:
13 12-A. School counselor. "School counselor" means a person who is employed as a
14 school counselor in a school setting and who:
15 A. Is certified as a school counselor by the department; or
16 B. Possesses a minimum of a master's degree in an approved program in guidance and
17 counseling.'
18 Amend the bill in section 4 in §12502 in the 2nd indented paragraph in the last line
19 (page 1, line 38 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "works in a school" and inserting
20 the following: 'is employed in a certified instructional or student support role, specifically
21 as a teacher, school counselor or licensed speech pathologist, in a school'
22 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
23 number to read consecutively.
24 SUMMARY
2255 This amendment adds a definition for "school counselor." The amendment also
2266 clarifies that the recipient of a loan repayment award must be employed in a certified
2277 instructional or student support role, specifically as a teacher, school counselor or licensed
2288 speech pathologist, in a school in an underserved geographic area.
2299 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
3300 (See attached)
Page 1 - 132LR0174(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
